12.41. The role of an external examiner in respect of external scrutiny of marking is:
a) to confirm, or otherwise, that academic standards and the achievements of students are appropriate and comparable with those in other UK higher education institutions of which
the external examiner has experience;
b) to confirm, or otherwise, that the assessment process has been conducted rigorously,
fairly, and in accordance with the University’s policies and regulations;
c) to confirm, or otherwise, that marking has been undertaken consistently and in accordance with agreed marking criteria.

